organic_results.title: The college channel: Private and public schools reconsidered
organic_results.snippet: Research on public and private schools has tended to focus on the presence and magnitude of differences in cognitive achievement. Using the data from the High School and Beyond parental sample, we assess another relevant outcome--college attendance. We find that seniors enrolled in private schools, whether Catholic or not, are significantly more likely to enter college in the fall of 1980 and to enroll in four-year institutions. These differences persist when academic track, ability levels, aspirations, and socioeconomic background are …
